      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "@Z5483 Thanks for working on this! I've ran into some `scripted-diff` issues as well, and I'm very excited to see that you're improving it :)\r\n\r\n@amitiuttarwar I'm a MacOS user as well, and I ran into the following issue; did you ever encounter this as well?\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ ./test/lint/commit-script-check.sh 85165d4~..85165d4\r\nsed: 1: \"/^-BEGIN VERIFY SCRIPT- ...\": unexpected EOF (pending }'s)\r\nError: missing script for: 85165d4332b0f72d30e0c584b476249b542338e6\r\nFailed\r\n```\r\n\r\nI fixed it locally by installing `gsed` and creating a symbolic link. But do you think it would make sense to add something like the following to help future MacOS users?\r\n\r\n<img width=\"905\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2020-09-16 at 3 31 54 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4276679/93399130-c2974180-f831-11ea-9459-dbd5e0425254.png\">\r\n\r\nAfter making this change, here's the new output:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ ./test/lint/commit-script-check.sh 85165d4~..85165d4\r\nsed: 1: \"/^-BEGIN VERIFY SCRIPT- ...\": unexpected EOF (pending }'s)\r\nError: Incompatible version of sed; MacOS users should install gsed\r\nFailed\r\n```",
